-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell D11 (matrix row 26): definer shadow of a method on a
-- MULTI-TYPARAM interface (`interface Ix a i`, two type params).  The d7 twin at
-- multi-typaram width: under the S2 INVERSION the module's own standalone
-- `get : Int -> Int -> Int` takes every occurrence, so the `Box` receiver is a
-- located REJECT (`Int vs Box`) and `get 3 1` -> 3.
-- Expected: check/run/build all REJECT (`Int vs Box`) at the `get (Box 3) 1` call.
--
-- ✅ S-3 FIXED 2026-07-17 (#54).  This cell was the corpus's last KNOWN-BAD row.
-- Every definer entry point gated on `singleParamIfaceMethod`, which -- despite
-- its name -- counts interface TYPE PARAMS, not method params, so `Ix a i`
-- bypassed the definer-shadow machinery entirely: check and build kept the OLD
-- pre-inversion per-receiver answer (4 then 3, per-receiver CORRECT!) while run,
-- which has no route stamp to follow and resolves the bare name lexically to the
-- standalone, E-PANICked `unknown op '*'` on a `Box`.  Two engines agreeing and
-- the third disagreeing is an S7 path-agreement violation.  The gate now pins the
-- fixed behavior; see its TABLE row.
interface Ix a i where
  get : a -> i -> Int

data Box = Box Int

impl Ix Box Int where
  get (Box n) i = n + i

get : Int -> Int -> Int
get n i = n * i

main =
  println (get (Box 3) 1)
  println (get 3 1)
